# Smart Classroom AI Agent Guide

## Project Documentation

This project uses centralized agent instructions in [`copilot-instructions.md`](../../.github/copilot-instructions.md) for all AI coding assistants.

## Available Automation Skills

When the task touches setup, startup, health checks, file upload/ingestion,
Q&A (RAG), or file management, discover and read the relevant `SKILL.md` under
[`.github/skills/`](../../.github/skills/). Prefer
[`skill-catalog.json`](../../.github/skills/skill-catalog.json) for routing, but
do not assume a fixed list of skill files.

Available skills:
- `sc-setup` — One-time setup: install dependencies and configure system
- `sc-up` — Start all services (backend, content search, frontend)
- `sc-doctor` — Check health, debug backend connectivity
- `sc-upload` — Upload and ingest files, poll until indexed
- `sc-qa` — Ask questions via the RAG Q&A endpoint
- `sc-files` — List, inspect, or delete indexed files; list tags

## Development Workflow & Conventions

- Prefer the repo's real interfaces:
  - Flutter setup: `utils/flutter/setup.ps1`
  - Flutter startup: `utils/flutter/start.ps1`
  - Content Search API at `http://127.0.0.1:9011`
  - Main backend API at `http://127.0.0.1:8000`
- Run commands from the repository root unless specified
- Run Flutter commands from `utils/flutter/`
- Skills invoke PowerShell scripts rather than executing commands directly
- Run commands in the real environment when possible and investigate failures
  before giving up